Hi everyone! Hector posted the ticket pricing for Banquet. Please take a look. If you have any questions/concerns please let us know.

Yesterday we had a PlexComm meeting and we decided to go with Mesa Verde. The reason was because it's really hard to book Student Center for those dates because we are competing with other clubs for a room. I already know my housemate's club are looking for a room the same dates as us. Yesterday we went to the event service office and they told us they cannot even tell us the dates for availability unless we fill out a form. Adina  is the only one who can fill that form out but we will have to wait for them to respond. We have to submit the deposit for Mesa Verde by the end of this week, so time is an issue because we need shit done asap, so if you really have any objection please let us know asap.

We already said that Banquet will be covered by ticket prices. From previous terms they are usually that expensive. I wish we could have told you all that you will be responsible for  your Big's tickets unfortunately we weren't allow to tell you until after reveal. 

Maybe you and your Big can work something out on paying for the ticket, but you still have to invite your Big personally to the banquet. If you still want to pay for your Bigs ticket and prefer a money plan or if you absolutely cannot afford the ticket please message us.

Also, there was some confusion during the meeting that caused 18 of you guys to vote for student center. fundraisers DO NOT cover most of banquet. The most we can make from each fundraising events is about $50-100 anyway. So technically even if we did a lot of fundraisers it's only going to cover our dj, photographers, and decorations. This was mentioned before and that's what usually happens prev terms as well. We are already asking for donations on decorations so if you want your banquet to look bomb af and not like cheap sh*t please help out. I'm down to donate any items we will be missing.

Student Center would have been cheaper but it's not that cheap either because we would then have to find a separate cater, rent the tables and chairs (each chairs.tables cost money), technicians (required to hire), etc. All that still adds up :( We liked Mesa Verde because we just pay for the food and no service charge and we can have the space for a long ass time. Also, we are most likely going to make profit from banquet tickets so all of that extra money will ROLL OVER to paying for our dues next term!!!

TL;DR we are doing the banquet at mesa verde if you have questions or concerns about pricing please message me or hector ASAP. Thanks!
